In MSTest v4, the `out` parameter overload of `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>` was removed. The method now **returns** the typed value directly.

**Fix:**

```csharp
// Before (v3)
Assert.IsInstanceOfType<MyType>(obj, out var typed);

// After (v4)
var typed = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<MyType>(obj);
```

The assertion still throws if `obj` is not an instance of `MyType`, and you get the typed variable back via the return value instead of an `out` parameter. Apply this pattern to all occurrences in your test file.

